<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT NON-DRIVE STEERING AXLE: ROCKWELL - ASSEMBLE - SEALS FOR THE KNUCKLE BUSHINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SEALS FOR THE KNUCKLE BUSHINGS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the top of the knuckle in a vise with brass jaws. The bottom of the knuckle must be
                toward you.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the seal in the bottom of the top knuckle bore. The lip of the seal must be away from
                the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200523">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200523" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200523" filename="../figg02/G0200523.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Installing the Bushing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the end cap for the knuckle on top of the seal. Slide the king pin through the opposite
                knuckle bore. Use the king pin to install the seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200524">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200524" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200524" filename="../figg02/G0200524.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Installing End Cap</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>For bronze bushings, make sure bottom of the seal touches the bushing.</para>
            <para>For Easy-Steer and plastic bushings, make sure the top of the seal is even with the top of the knuckle
                machined surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200525">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200525" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200525" filename="../figg02/G0200525.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Seal Aligned With Top of Knuckle</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the knuckle over in the vise. The jaws of the vise must hold the bottom of the knuckle
                and the top of the knuckle must be toward you.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the seal in the top of the bottom knuckle bore. The lip of the seal must be away from
                the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200523">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat step 3 of this procedure.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
